 wonder, and ominous danger that characterizes Modiano's most rewarding fiction.  Special feature: J. M. G. Le Clézio's foreword, here in English for the first time, provides a rare and insightful appreciation of one Nobel laureate by another.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 0aBoarding schoolszFrancezParisvFiction. 0aTeenage boyszFrancezParisvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aLe Clézio, J. M. G.1 aPolizzotti, Mark08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300231588423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300231588.jpg  a978-3-11-063898-1  YUP eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles